  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Future Proofing African Cities for Sustainable Growth</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UK&#x2019;s &#xA3;4.915 million will fund a project to support at least 8 cities in Africa to become future proofed to climate, environment and natural resource challenges, so that they are inclusive and resilient, and have growing economies.  It will help make cities work for the urban poor. It will conduct an in depth feasibility and scoping study and develop innovative tools to enable rapidly growing African cities to realise their potential as centres of growth and job creation; use research and evidence to develop targeted urban action plans; and will deliver research new research to fill data and evidence gaps to maximise sustainable economic growth.</narrative>
  </description>
